# Admin Layout Consistency

When editing or creating admin pages/components, match the existing admin baseline layout used by `Main Dashboard`.

- Use the shared container baseline from `AdminShell` (`.content`) for width and horizontal rhythm.
- Keep page-level headers consistent: icon + title + optional subtitle on the left, back/navigation action on the right.
- Ensure `Back to Dashboard` is always present in admin pages using the page-level pattern:
  - top-right button in header
  - bottom-left button near page end
- Keep back-button size and spacing consistent across admin pages.
- Avoid reintroducing boxed or sticky header bars unless explicitly requested for a specific page.
- Use consistent card geometry (border radius, border weight, spacing) with current admin pages.
- Keep section spacing and vertical rhythm aligned with existing dashboard/admin tool pages.
- Preserve mobile responsiveness with the same breakpoints and behavior already used in admin styles.
- For admin tools pages, keep back-navigation placement consistent with current convention when requested.

## Quick checks before finishing

- Header alignment and spacing visually matches other admin pages.
- Top-right and bottom-left `Back to Dashboard` buttons are present and visually consistent.
- Left/right gutters are consistent with the shared admin container.
- Card/list/table blocks do not look denser or wider than sibling admin pages.
- No page-specific CSS overrides that break the shared layout baseline.
